This paper discusses the unsupervised learning of conceptual systems, which involves the extraction and naming of concepts from noisy perceptual experience. This topic is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), natural language processing (cs.CL), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper, ordered from most to least likely.
